page.title: 08 Housing In Our 'D' Block
page.content: Our area contains a variety of housing differing in age, style and construction, primarily situated in groups to form the villages of Great and Lt.Maplestead, Wickham St.Paul and Gestingthorpe. Large farmhouses, with their attendant workers' cottages, barns converted to residential use, Victorian houses and terraced cottages, post war council houses, modern bungalows and detached homes all contribute to an eclectic housing heritage. Of particular interest are many good examples of mediaeval timber frame dwellings, both large and small - in some cases with original wattle and daub/lath and plaster walling - others brick faced and rendered at a later date. Examples: Parks Farm,Moat Farm, September Cottage, Pannell's Ash Greenview,Gallants & Stonehouse Farm.
